FBIS3-58429 "drweu009_j_94009" FBIS-WEU-94-009 Document Type:Daily Report 13 Jan 1994 ITALY & VATICAN CITY Giugni: Economy Has `Structural' Disadvantages LD1201191094 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1521 GMT 12 Jan 94 LD1201191094 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext Language: Italian Article Type:BFN [Text] Italy lacks at least three million jobs. This is a "structural" disadvantage compared to other European countries which, together with a low level of education, makes the Italian situation especially difficult. This was said by Labor Minister Giugni at the presentation of a study of medium-term prospects for the labor market. Giugni said that in October employment fell by 550,000 units compared with October 1992 and numbers unemployed increased by 350,000 units, while the unemployment rate went up from 9.7 percent to 11.3 percent.
